<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 10:06PM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central St. Clair
and northeastern Vernon Counties through 1045 PM CDT...
At 1006 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Schell City, or 7 miles southeast of Rich Hill, moving
east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Truman Lake...                    Appleton City...
Osceola...                        Lowry City...
Schell City...                    Roscoe...
Vista...                          Harwood...
Tiffin...                         Johnson City...
Taberville...                     Monegaw Springs...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
